The paper deals with the representation of graphs and hypergraphs using geometric objects in 3D space, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of polygons and their touching relationships also suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the existence and non-existence of certain types of representations, which is related to graph theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.DS). Finally, the construction of representations for specific graph classes involves algorithms and data structures (cs.GR).
